# Rust Review Tools

Use these commands selectively. Prefer repository-documented commands first.

## Baseline

Inspect:

```bash
ls
find . -maxdepth 4 -type f \( \
  -name "Cargo.toml" -o \
  -name "Cargo.lock" -o \
  -name "rust-toolchain.toml" -o \
  -name "build.rs" -o \
  -name "Makefile" -o \
  -name "justfile" -o \
  -name "Dockerfile" \
\)
find .github/workflows -type f 2>/dev/null
```

Run as applicable:

```bash
cargo check --workspace --all-targets
cargo test --workspace
cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings
cargo fmt --check
```

If appropriate:

```bash
cargo check --workspace --all-targets --all-features
cargo test --workspace --all-features
cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings
```

If features are mutually exclusive, do not blindly use `--all-features`. Inspect the feature matrix and run documented combinations.

Stop if the baseline fails.

## Mapping

```bash
find . -maxdepth 4 -type f \( \
  -path "*/src/main.rs" -o \
  -path "*/src/lib.rs" -o \
  -path "*/src/bin/*.rs" -o \
  -path "*/examples/*.rs" -o \
  -path "*/benches/*.rs" -o \
  -path "*/tests/*.rs" -o \
  -name "build.rs" \
\)

cargo metadata --no-deps
rg "^\[features\]|^\[workspace\]|^\[dependencies\]" Cargo.toml
```

Framework/entry-point checks:

```bash
rg "Router::new|\.route\(|\.nest\(|\.merge\("
rg "#\[.*route|HttpServer|App::new|service\("
rg "clap|Parser|Subcommand|Command"
rg "tokio::spawn|spawn_blocking|JoinHandle"
rg "macro_rules!|proc_macro|derive\("
rg "include_str!|include_bytes!|env!|option_env!"
```

Inspect:

- `src/main.rs`
- `src/lib.rs`
- `src/bin/*`
- `examples/*`
- `benches/*`
- `tests/*`
- `build.rs`
- `crates/*`
- `xtask/*`
- `.cargo/config.toml`
- CI and Docker files

## Dependency hygiene

Use these as signals, not final proof.

```bash
cargo machete
cargo +nightly udeps --workspace --all-targets
cargo tree
cargo metadata --no-deps
```

For a suspicious dependency:

```bash
cargo tree -i <crate>
rg "<crate_name>|use .*<crate_name>|extern crate <crate_name>"
```

Notes:

- `cargo machete` is fast but imprecise.
- `cargo udeps` requires nightly.
- Optional dependencies may be used only behind features.
- Dependencies may exist for feature unification or build scripts.

## Dead/unused signals

```bash
cargo check --workspace --all-targets
cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets
RUSTFLAGS="-D warnings" cargo check --workspace --all-targets
rg "allow\(dead_code\)|allow\(unused\)|deprecated|TODO|FIXME"
```

Compiler silence is not proof that public API is removable.

## Reference checks

```bash
rg "<symbol_or_filename>"
rg "mod <module>|pub mod <module>|use .*<symbol>"
rg "pub use .*<symbol>|pub mod"
rg "#\[cfg|cfg\("
rg "#\[derive|serde|Deserialize|Serialize"
rg "From<|Into<|TryFrom<|Display|Debug|Error"
rg "unsafe|unwrap\(|expect\(|todo!\(|unimplemented!\(|panic!\("
```

## Complexity and maintainability

```bash
cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features
tokei
scc
rg "clone\(|Arc<Mutex|Box<dyn|async_trait|unsafe"
```

## Redundant data access

```bash
rg "for .* in .*\.iter\(|for .* in .*"
rg "sqlx::query|diesel|sea_orm|query_as|execute\("
rg "reqwest|hyper|tonic|grpc"
rg "spawn_blocking|block_in_place"
```

Look for DB/HTTP calls inside loops, repeated round-trips, blocking I/O in async contexts, over-fetching, and missing batching/caching.

## Verify before flagging

Check suspects against:

- public library API and re-exports from `lib.rs`
- binary entry points and `src/bin`
- examples, benches, integration tests
- feature-gated paths and platform-specific `cfg`
- macros and proc macros
- trait implementations used indirectly
- Serde derives/deserialization
- Clap command registration
- Axum/Actix/Poem/Rocket route registration
- Tokio background tasks
- build scripts and generated code
- FFI boundaries
- `include_str!`, `include_bytes!`, `env!`, or config references
- workspace dependency usage
- CI, Docker, deploy, or infra references
- external/public consumers of library crates

## Do not treat as dead unless proven

- public APIs and anything re-exported from `lib.rs`
- trait impls
- derive-based serialization/deserialization paths
- macro-generated code and proc-macro inputs
- feature-gated code
- platform-specific `cfg` code
- build scripts and generated code
- FFI bindings
- `src/bin` binaries
- examples and benches
- integration-test helpers
- CLI commands
- route handlers registered by macro or builder pattern
- background tasks
- unsafe abstractions
- anything referenced by deploy, Docker, CI, or infra config

## Rust-specific caution

Be especially careful with:

- `pub` items in library crates
- feature flags that are not enabled by default
- `cfg(target_os = "...")`
- trait implementations used through generics
- Serde `Deserialize` structs constructed from external input
- `From`, `Into`, `TryFrom`, `Display`, `Debug`, and `Error` impls
- async traits
- macro inputs
- build-time generated files
- optional dependencies used only under specific features
- dependencies used only for feature unification

## Git and impact

Use Git signals for “abandoned” only, never as proof of dead code.

```bash
git log -1 --format=%cr -- <file>
git blame <file>
wc -l <file>
git diff --stat
```

